properties.Name: ProductRatingFactorValue
properties.Description:
The Rating Multiplier or Amount associated with an Insurance Product Rating Factor during the designated period.

All multipliers should be applied to the base rate and then incremented by the values for all applicable values.

For example: 
Factor Type of "Sex" with value "Male" has an associated Rating Multiplier of 1.5
Factor Type of "Age" with value "50" has an associated Rating Multiplier of 0.90
Factor Type of "Occupation" with value of "Retired" has an associated Rating Amount of -50
Policy Premium would be calculated as Base Premium * 1.5 * 0.90 + -50

Columns.Name: ProductRatingFactorRatingMultiplier
Columns.Description: The multiplier associated with the Product Rating Factor for the given Value for the given period.

Columns.Name: ProductRatingFactorRatingAmount
Columns.Description: The Amount associated with the Product Rating Factor for the given Value for the given period.

Columns.Name: ProductRatingFactorValueNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the Product Rating Factor Value.
